<html>
<head>
    <title>SpamTrawler Plugin Installation Instructions</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Installation instructions for "{$pluginname}"</h1>
<ol>
    <li>Unpack the "{$pluginname}.zip" file (Right Click -> Unpack to {$pluginname})</li>
    <li>Upload the resulting directory to: /application/modules/Firewall/</li>
    <li>Login to your SpamTrawler Admin Panel</li>
    <li>Navigate to: Settings -> Firewall -> Install Plugins</li>
    <li>Click: Browse</li>
    <li>Choose the "install.json" file that came with this plugin</li>
    <li>Click: Upload</li>
    <li>The plugin will now be installed into the database</li>
</ol>
<p>The installed plugin is now ready to be configured (Settings Tab)</p>

<p>New plugins are always added to the end of the plugin list within their particular section.</p>

<p>To change the position of a particular plugin, please drag&drop the plugin into the desired position, and click the
    "Save" button</p>
</body>
</html>
